1.6 Reliability and Fault Tolerance

Theorem 1.4 (Radiation-Induced Error Rate). For memory of size M bits with SEU rate \lambda per bit-day, using SECDED ECC, the probability of an uncorrectable error in time \Delta t is bounded by:

P_{UE} < \frac{M}{2^{22}} (\lambda \Delta t)^2

Proof. SECDED detects all 1- and 2-bit errors in a word. An undetected error requires ≥3 bits flipping in patterns that map to valid codewords, probability < 2^{-22} per word. A double-bit error in same word has probability \approx (\lambda \Delta t)^2. With M bits, union bound gives the result. ∎

Conservative Numbers: For commercial GPU memory in LEO, \lambda \approx 10^{-5} \ \text{/bit-day}. For M = 16 \ \text{TB} = 1.28\times10^{14} bits over \Delta t = 1.5 \ \text{hr}:

P_{UE} < \frac{1.28\times10^{14}}{4.2\times10^6} (10^{-5} \times 0.0625)^2 \approx 1.2\times10^{-11}

This supports "<10^{-10} per orbit" as a conservative, defensible claim.

