2.3 Validated Software & Fault Tolerance

Incorporating lessons from Google Suncatcher:

· Radiation Tolerance: Commercial accelerators (TPU/GPU) can survive LEO doses (~15 krad over 5 yrs) with selective shielding of critical components.
· Fault Strategy: Combine hardware ECC with algorithm-based fault tolerance (ABFT) for matrix ops and selective checkpointing.
· Checkpoint Optimization: Only save model parameters (not optimizer state), compress 4:1. For a 50B parameter model at FP16: Checkpoint size ≈ 100 GB → 25 GB stored. With 100 Gbps laser downlink: ≈ 2 seconds to transmit.

Communication Architecture:

· Primary: 4 × 25 Gbps optical links to ground. Availability >99% via geographic diversity.
· Intersatellite (Future): 100 Gbps optical crosslinks, validated by Google's formation-flying plan for <1 km spacing.

