3. Defensible Performance Proofs & Bounds

3.1 Throughput: Conservative Lower Bound

Theorem 3.1 (Orbital Throughput Bound). For an OCN with average compute power \overline{P_c} over orbit period T, and computational efficiency \eta_{comp} (TFLOPS/W), the sustained throughput is bounded by:

\mathcal{T} \geq \frac{\overline{P_c} \cdot T \cdot \eta_{comp}}{3600} \ \text{TFLOPS-hr}

Proof. The average power \overline{P_c} is constrained by the energy-neutrality condition from Lemma 1.2. The product \overline{P_c} \cdot T is the total energy allocated to compute per orbit. Dividing by energy per FLOP (1/\eta_{comp}) gives total FLOPs, and dividing by 3600 gives TFLOPS-hr. ∎

Conservative Calculation:

· From Table 2.1: \overline{P_c} \approx 22 \ \text{kW} (factoring states S0-S4)
· \eta_{comp} = 1 / 70 \ \text{W/TFLOPS} (derated from peak 50 W/TFLOPS)
· T = 1.5 \ \text{hr}

\mathcal{T} \geq \frac{22000 \times 1.5 \times (1/70)}{3600} \approx 280 \ \text{TFLOPS-hr}

Realistic Range: 280–350 TFLOPS-hr/orbit, matching the "conservative view" from the critique.

